@vishh I'd like to avoid revendoring anything else than gRPC and it's dependecies (x/net and x/text).
I really think that doing so is outside the scope of this PR and would need to go through the whole re-testing on a 100 node cluster.

Let's keep the changes to the minimum to avoid breaking anything else :)

The entanglement is more complex than i thought. Apart from the core client, k8s.io/metrics is [importing]("https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/vendor/k8s.io/metrics/pkg/apis/metrics/v1alpha1/types.go#L21") "k8s.io/client-go/pkg/api/v1" as well. It's going to block us from moving external types to another repo in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/44784.

One expedient solution is moving the entire vendor/k8s.io/metric to thirdparty/forked and manually take care the dependency until we get rid of the staging. [edit] Or move k8s.io/metrics to staging, then we don't need to rewrite the import path...

@sttts @DirectXMan12 @lavalamp what do you think?
